						<summary>

						<p>On a stone near the tank.</p>						

						<p>1121 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the Chālukya-Vikrama year 46, Plava, Jyēshṭha śu. 2 Sunday. Dakshiṇāyana-saṅkramaṇa. The Saṅkramaṇa occurred on Āshāḍha śu. 9 of the year, corresponding to 1121 A.D., June 26, which fell on a Sunday. This seems to be the intended date. Otherwise the given details correspond to 1121 A.D., May 20.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of land to a god by <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Pemmāḍi. It mentions Dēsura Bammaya-nāyaka. The inscription is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
